  "script": "Two pigs, same morning? Woodbridge, Connecticut woke up to a problem with hooves. Two pigs, two different streets, same tiny town, same morning. The first one's spotted at 5:45 a.m., trespassing through a yard on Old Quarry Road. Cute, weird, whatever — until a SECOND call comes in from Acorn Hill Road, where a totally different pig has apparently been living its best life for 2 days straight. Now it's a full pig-hunt: animal control, cops from 2 other towns, and a very confused vet, all chasing bacon through the suburbs. They corner one. The other? Still out there, living free. And here's the kicker — nobody knows whose pigs these even are. So who loses a pig on Old Quarry Road and just… doesn't notice?",
